  "prompt": "Who is Amartya Sen?",
  "response": "Amartya Sen is an Indian economist, philosopher, and Nobel Prize laureate, widely regarded as one of the most influential social scientists of the 20th and early 21st centuries. Here are some key details about him:\n\n1. Background:\n- Born on November 3, 1933, in Santiniketan, West Bengal, India\n- Studied at Presidency College, Calcutta, and Trinity College, Cambridge\n\n2. Academic Achievements:\n- Professor at multiple prestigious universities, including Oxford, Cambridge, and Harvard\n- Considered a pioneer in welfare economics and development theory\n- Known for his work on welfare economics, social choice theory, and economic development\n\n3. Nobel Prize:\n- Won the Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences in 1998\n- Recognized for his contributions to welfare economics and social choice theory\n\n4. Major Contributions:\n- Developed the \"capability approach\" to human development\n- Worked extensively on issues of poverty, famines, and social justice\n- Advocated for understanding poverty beyond mere income metrics\n\n5. Other Notable Achievements:\n- Author of numerous influential books like \"Development as Freedom\"\n- Received multiple international awards and honors\n- Renowned for his interdisciplinary approach combining economics, philosophy, and social sciences\n\nSen is considered a leading intellectual who has significantly influenced thinking about economic development, social welfare, and human rights.",
